metadata.title: Special Report No. 29, Physical and chemical data from the Bering Sea, North Pacific Ocean and Gulf of Alaska - Brown Bear cruise 176, July - September 1957 for the International Geophysical Year of 1957-58.
metadata.description: The major objectives of the cruise, in terms of the IGY program were to obtain detailed observations from the deep waters, including those in the Aleutian Trench and to determine, if possible, the nature of the water exchange between the Northern Pacific and the Bering Sea.
